caller_intent: Grid Valencia is seeking clarification on why their 2019 Volkswagen's insurance coverage was downgraded from full coverage to liability-only, and how to potentially restore full coverage, particularly after a totaled car incident.
resolution_steps: Agent Heather explains that coverage was likely removed in 2024 due to Jose (a household member) failing to provide license information, which is required for full coverage.
Heather clarifies that lienholders typically require full coverage, and the removal may have been triggered by Jose's lack of licensing.
Heather offers to investigate further to determine if the coverage change can be reversed, acknowledging the totaled car situation.
Caller agrees to wait for Heather's follow-up call the next day after lunch.
knowledge_required: Insurance policy requirements for lienholders and full coverage
Impact of household members' licensing status on policy changes
Process for reversing policy changes due to missing documentation
systems_referenced: Insurance carrier's policy database (implied through discussion of coverage changes)
summary: Grid Valencia discovered their Volkswagen's insurance was liability-only after a totaled car incident and sought clarification. The agent explained the coverage change likely stemmed from missing license info from a household member (Jose). The agent offered to investigate further and agreed to follow up the next day.
